# JAVA MULTITHREADING — COMPLETE NOTES

## 1. Multitasking kya hai?

Multitasking ka matlab hai ek system par multiple tasks ko ek saath ya apparently ek saath execute karna.

Example:

- Music chal raha hai
- File download ho rahi hai
- Browser open hai
- Code compile ho raha hai

Multitasking do main types ki hoti hai:

1. Process-based multitasking
2. Thread-based multitasking


============================================================
2. PROCESS KYA HAI?
============================================================

Process ek running program hota hai.

Example:

Chrome
IntelliJ IDEA
DataGrip
Spotify

Jab koi application run hoti hai, operating system uske liye ek process create karta hai.

Example:

IntelliJ IDEA
      ↓
    Process


============================================================
3. THREAD KYA HAI?
============================================================

Thread ek process ke andar execution ka ek path hota hai.

Ek process ke andar multiple threads ho sakte hain.

Example:

Music Application
       |
       |--- Thread 1 → Music Play
       |
       |--- Thread 2 → Download Song
       |
       |--- Thread 3 → Update UI


Simple Definition:

Thread is a lightweight unit of execution inside a process.


============================================================
4. PROCESS VS THREAD
============================================================

PROCESS:

- Independent running program
- More memory use karta hai
- Process creation expensive hoti hai
- Processes ke beech communication relatively difficult hota hai


THREAD:

- Process ke andar execution unit
- Lightweight hota hai
- Same process ke threads memory/resources share kar sakte hain
- Thread creation generally cheaper hoti hai


Example:

Process
   |
   |--- Thread 1
   |--- Thread 2
   |--- Thread 3


============================================================
5. MULTITHREADING KYA HAI?
============================================================

Ek process ke andar multiple threads ka concurrent execution multithreading kehlata hai.

Example:

Web Server
    |
    |--- Request 1
    |--- Request 2
    |--- Request 3


Benefits:

- Better responsiveness
- Multiple tasks handle kar sakte hain
- CPU resources ka better utilization ho sakta hai
- Background tasks execute kar sakte hain
- Server applications me multiple requests handle karne me useful


Important:

Multithreading ka matlab hamesha true parallel execution nahi hota.

Threads:

- Concurrently execute ho sakte hain
- Multi-core CPU par parallel bhi execute ho sakte hain


============================================================
6. CONCURRENCY VS PARALLELISM
============================================================

CONCURRENCY:

Multiple tasks progress kar rahe hain.

Example:

Task A
Task B
Task C

CPU inke beech switch kar sakta hai.


PARALLELISM:

Multiple tasks literally same time par execute ho rahe hain.

Example:

Core 1 → Task A
Core 2 → Task B


Simple:

Concurrency = Multiple tasks in progress

Parallelism = Multiple tasks executing simultaneously


