10. start() VS run()
============================================================

Bahut important interview question.


-------------------------
run()
-------------------------

thread.run();

Ye normal method call hai.

New thread create nahi hota.

Current thread hi run() execute karta hai.


Example:

Thread t = new Thread(() -> {

    System.out.println(
            Thread.currentThread().getName()
    );

});

t.run();


Output:

main


-------------------------
start()
-------------------------

thread.start();

Ye new thread start karta hai.

JVM/Thread implementation new thread ke execution me run() method ko invoke karti hai.


Example:

Thread t = new Thread(() -> {

    System.out.println(
            Thread.currentThread().getName()
    );

});

t.start();


Possible Output:

Thread-0


Summary:

run()
    ↓
Normal Method Call
    ↓
Current Thread


start()
    ↓
New Thread Starts
    ↓
run() executes on new thread


IMPORTANT:

Ek Thread object ko generally sirf ek baar start kar sakte hain.

Example:

t.start();
t.start();

Second start par:

IllegalThreadStateException


