31. ATOMICITY
============================================================

Atomic operation wo hota hai jo indivisible operation ki tarah behave karta hai.

Example:

count++;

compound operation hai.


Atomic classes:

AtomicInteger
AtomicLong
AtomicBoolean


Example:

import java.util.concurrent.atomic.AtomicInteger;


class Counter {

    private AtomicInteger count =
            new AtomicInteger(0);


    public void increment() {

        count.incrementAndGet();
    }


    public int getCount() {

        return count.get();
    }
}


Ye simple counter use cases me synchronized ka alternative ho sakta hai.


