32. DEADLOCK
============================================================

Deadlock tab hota hai jab threads ek dusre ke resources/locks ka wait karte rehte hain aur progress nahi hoti.


Example:

Thread 1:

Lock A acquired
Waiting for Lock B


Thread 2:

Lock B acquired
Waiting for Lock A


Result:

Thread 1 waits for Thread 2

Thread 2 waits for Thread 1

Both wait indefinitely.


Diagram:

Thread 1
   |
Has Lock A
   |
Needs Lock B
   |
   ↓

Thread 2
   |
Has Lock B
   |
Needs Lock A


DEADLOCK


============================================================
33. DEADLOCK EXAMPLE
============================================================

Object lockA = new Object();
Object lockB = new Object();


Thread t1 = new Thread(() -> {

    synchronized (lockA) {

        synchronized (lockB) {

            System.out.println("Task 1");
        }
    }

});


Thread t2 = new Thread(() -> {

    synchronized (lockB) {

        synchronized (lockA) {

            System.out.println("Task 2");
        }
    }

});


Potential deadlock:

t1 has lockA
t2 has lockB

t1 waits for lockB
t2 waits for lockA


============================================================
34. DEADLOCK PREVENTION
============================================================

Common practices:

1. Locks same order me acquire karo

Example:

Thread 1:

Lock A
then
Lock B


Thread 2:

Lock A
then
Lock B


2. Unnecessary nested locks avoid karo

3. Critical sections small rakho

4. Higher-level concurrency utilities use karo

5. Explicit locks use karte waqt tryLock() jaise mechanisms useful ho sakte hain


